          <name>CAPTURE_ALL_TOUCH_AFTER_START</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>If this actor receives a touch-start event, then all following touch events are sent to this actor until a touch-end. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;captureAllTouchAfterStart&quot;, type <ref refid="classDali_1_1Property_1ab466e94d7adc55576e8e86ee96db565da538a12b1a95a82f6dae06b9cf7835df7" kindref="member">Property::BOOLEAN</ref> <simplesect kind="note"><para>Default is false, i.e. actor under touch event will receive the touch even if touch started on this actor </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1DevelActor_1_1Property_1aa1134c47f9a05b9a43b780937f4fa8dfa31649802d5f45d5bdf030ced6a482afa" prot="public">
          <name>TOUCH_AREA_MARGIN</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>If you set the TOUCH_AREA_MARGIN on an actor, when you touch the actor, the touch area is expand from the size of actor. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;touchAreaMargin&quot;, type <ref refid="classDali_1_1Property_1ab466e94d7adc55576e8e86ee96db565da77993d8ecbf2d9cf05dfb42c40df1279" kindref="member">Property::EXTENTS</ref>. For example <programlisting filename=".cpp"><codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><ref refid="classDali_1_1Actor" kindref="compound">Actor</ref><sp/>actor<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="classDali_1_1Actor_1afbc2ddbec114fadcb5631e9afa3abfb5" kindref="member">Actor::New</ref>();</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/>actor.<ref refid="classDali_1_1Handle_1a5785113e2869597bd7da03b36aab2fbf" kindref="member">SetProperty</ref>(<ref refid="structDali_1_1Actor_1_1Property_1aa00cf4d2c81c442d5bf5c544f96410c3a6e55596f175e7c1a557b65f0a6f25f23" kindref="member">Actor::Property::SIZE</ref>,<sp/><ref refid="structDali_1_1Vector2" kindref="compound">Vector2</ref>(20.0f,<sp/>20.0f));</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/>actor.<ref refid="classDali_1_1Handle_1a5785113e2869597bd7da03b36aab2fbf" kindref="member">SetProperty</ref>(<ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1DevelActor_1_1Property_1aa1134c47f9a05b9a43b780937f4fa8dfa31649802d5f45d5bdf030ced6a482afa" kindref="member">DevelActor::Property::TOUCH_AREA_MARGIN</ref>,<sp/><ref refid="structDali_1_1Extents" kindref="compound">Extents</ref>(10,<sp/>20,<sp/>30,<sp/>40));</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/>actor.<ref refid="classDali_1_1Actor_1ada69138deca6823d7c4432de705a49d9" kindref="member">TouchedSignal</ref>().Connect(OnTouchCallback);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">+---------------------+</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>^<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|<sp/><sp/>30<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>+----+----+<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/>10<sp/>|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|<sp/>20<sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|&lt;---+<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>+-----&gt;|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>+----+----+<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|<sp/>40<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">|<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>v<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>|</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">+---------------------+</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> The actual touched size is actor.width + touchAreaOffset.start + touchAreaOffset.end and actor.height + touchAreaOffset.top + touchAreaOffset.bottom </para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1DevelActor_1_1Property_1aa1134c47f9a05b9a43b780937f4fa8dfa70dc1ac88e261948d0847f64cb74f6c9" prot="public">
          <name>BLEND_EQUATION</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Determines which blend equation will be used to render renderers of this actor. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="pre"><para>To use Advanced Blend Equation(<ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1DevelBlendEquation_1ab2e996b8c1594db5ebe826e3b8c262e2a3f27ebd2f001546ac7d829eda5c33fb2" kindref="member">DevelBlendEquation::MULTIPLY</ref> ~ <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1DevelBlendEquation_1ab2e996b8c1594db5ebe826e3b8c262e2ad23e3c8b8b8f172ef0de4a9c55ac267f" kindref="member">DevelBlendEquation::LUMINOSITY</ref>), the color to be rendered should be pre-multipled alpha.</para>
</simplesect>
Name &quot;blendEquation&quot;, type <ref refid="classDali_1_1Property_1ab466e94d7adc55576e8e86ee96db565dac3c145c2e414f3ec168a6f4fb8968c5b" kindref="member">Property::INTEGER</ref>. <simplesect kind="note"><para><ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Color" kindref="compound">Color</ref> of each renderer will be blended with rendering framebuffer. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>To check the blend equation is supported in the system, use <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Capabilities_1acb17c43232a2e7fdbed03d4ee8ab3b05" kindref="member">Dali::Capabilities::IsBlendEquationSupported</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1DevelActor_1_1Property_1aa1134c47f9a05b9a43b780937f4fa8dfa75dd6691fa72dde6529105e78224870c" prot="public">
          <name>TOUCH_FOCUSABLE</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Sets whether this actor can focus by touch. If user sets this to true, the actor will be focused when user touch it. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classDali_1_1Actor" kindref="compound">Actor</ref><sp/>actor<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="classDali_1_1Actor_1afbc2ddbec114fadcb5631e9afa3abfb5" kindref="member">Actor::New</ref>();</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">actor.<ref refid="classDali_1_1Handle_1a5785113e2869597bd7da03b36aab2fbf" kindref="member">SetProperty</ref>(<ref refid="structDali_1_1Actor_1_1Property_1aa00cf4d2c81c442d5bf5c544f96410c3ae32d7408a8d0a0161aa2fa247e13fb42" kindref="member">Actor::Property::KEYBOARD_FOCUSABLE</ref>,<sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">true</highlight><highlight class="normal">);<sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>whether<sp/>the<sp/>actor<sp/>can<sp/>have<sp/>focus<sp/>or<sp/>not<sp/>with<sp/>keyboard<sp/>navigation.</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">actor.<ref refid="classDali_1_1Handle_1a5785113e2869597bd7da03b36aab2fbf" kindref="member">SetProperty</ref>(<ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1DevelActor_1_1Property_1aa1134c47f9a05b9a43b780937f4fa8dfa75dd6691fa72dde6529105e78224870c" kindref="member">DevelActor::Property::TOUCH_FOCUSABLE</ref>,<sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">true</highlight><highlight class="normal">);<sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>Whether<sp/>the<sp/>user<sp/>can<sp/>focus<sp/>by<sp/>touch,<sp/>user<sp/>can<sp/>set<sp/>focus<sp/>by<sp/>touching<sp/>the<sp/>actor.</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Name &quot;touchFocusable&quot;, type <ref refid="classDali_1_1Property_1ab466e94d7adc55576e8e86ee96db565da538a12b1a95a82f6dae06b9cf7835df7" kindref="member">Property::BOOLEAN</ref>. </para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1DevelActor_1_1Property_1aa1134c47f9a05b9a43b780937f4fa8dfa96bd000a34861716ce80fac1ecaff732" prot="public">
          <name>KEYBOARD_FOCUSABLE_CHILDREN</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Whether the children of this actor can be focusable by keyboard navigation. If user sets this to false, the children of this actor will not be focused. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;keyboardFocusableChildren&quot;, type <ref refid="classDali_1_1Property_1ab466e94d7adc55576e8e86ee96db565da538a12b1a95a82f6dae06b9cf7835df7" kindref="member">Property::BOOLEAN</ref>. <simplesect kind="note"><para>Default value is true. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1DevelActor_1_1Property_1aa1134c47f9a05b9a43b780937f4fa8dfa1a3f12dd403d227bd406faf74900bf8a" prot="public">
          <name>USER_INTERACTION_ENABLED</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The flag whether the actor should be enabled all user interaction including touch, focus and activation. this value have higher priority over the sensitve and focusable in negative action. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;userInteractionEnabled&quot;, type <ref refid="classDali_1_1Property_1ab466e94d7adc55576e8e86ee96db565da538a12b1a95a82f6dae06b9cf7835df7" kindref="member">Property::BOOLEAN</ref>. <simplesect kind="note"><para>Default value is true. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1DevelActor_1_1Property_1aa1134c47f9a05b9a43b780937f4fa8dfa95393faa0f52ee344c0712734dd7be21" prot="public">
          <name>ALLOW_ONLY_OWN_TOUCH</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>It only receive for touch events that started from itself. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;allowOnlyOwnTouch&quot;, type <ref refid="classDali_1_1Property_1ab466e94d7adc55576e8e86ee96db565da538a12b1a95a82f6dae06b9cf7835df7" kindref="member">Property::BOOLEAN</ref> <simplesect kind="note"><para>Default is false. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1DevelActor_1_1Property_1aa1134c47f9a05b9a43b780937f4fa8dfaa0905a318858e9c11a4dd613ef0b0ab6" prot="public">
          <name>USE_TEXTURE_UPDATE_AREA</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Whether the actor uses the update area of the texture instead of its own. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;useTextureUpdateArea&quot;, type <ref refid="classDali_1_1Property_1ab466e94d7adc55576e8e86ee96db565da538a12b1a95a82f6dae06b9cf7835df7" kindref="member">Property::BOOLEAN</ref> <simplesect kind="note"><para>Default is false. If this set true, the value of <ref refid="structDali_1_1Actor_1_1Property_1aa00cf4d2c81c442d5bf5c544f96410c3af60510353b78806d44c465b255cd1f28" kindref="member">Actor::Property::UPDATE_AREA_HINT</ref> is ignored and we assume the sizes of the actor and the texture are same. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1DevelActor_1_1Property_1aa1134c47f9a05b9a43b780937f4fa8dfa60fec776f8464be04f506285a65f97f8" prot="public">
          <name>DISPATCH_TOUCH_MOTION</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Whether to send touch motion events or not. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;dispatchTouchMotion&quot;, type <ref refid="classDali_1_1Property_1ab466e94d7adc55576e8e86ee96db565da538a12b1a95a82f6dae06b9cf7835df7" kindref="member">Property::BOOLEAN</ref> <simplesect kind="note"><para>Default is true. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1DevelActor_1_1Property_1aa1134c47f9a05b9a43b780937f4fa8dfacd565f374157d2c434e53714831e7b41" prot="public">
          <name>DISPATCH_HOVER_MOTION</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Whether to send hover motion events or not. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;dispatchHoverMotion&quot;, type <ref refid="classDali_1_1Property_1ab466e94d7adc55576e8e86ee96db565da538a12b1a95a82f6dae06b9cf7835df7" kindref="member">Property::BOOLEAN</ref> <simplesect kind="note"><para>Default is true. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1DevelActor_1_1Property_1aa1134c47f9a05b9a43b780937f4fa8dfaf8a56b2afecd08a49242dee006195192" prot="public">
          <name>CHILDREN_DEPTH_INDEX_POLICY</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The policy of depth index generate. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;childrenDepthIndexPolicy&quot;, type <ref refid="classDali_1_1Property_1ab466e94d7adc55576e8e86ee96db565dac3c145c2e414f3ec168a6f4fb8968c5b" kindref="member">Property::INTEGER</ref> <simplesect kind="note"><para>Default is <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1DevelActor_1_1ChildrenDepthIndexPolicy_1a2b2b0576b9223095ffcaf7864833df3aa644b4552fd9aaf56118f3ab6f085f878" kindref="member">ChildrenDepthIndexPolicy::Type::INCREASE</ref>. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Only has effort under Behavior::LAYER_UI. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1DevelActor_1_1Property_1aa1134c47f9a05b9a43b780937f4fa8dfa95cba0c189ff2f622c42505683aa2665" prot="public">
          <name>IGNORED</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The flag to identify whether the <ref refid="classDali_1_1Actor" kindref="compound">Actor</ref> and it&apos;s descendants are ignored or not. If true, it will not be rendered and will be excluded from render thread computation. </para>
